<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.01102/2½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Commission to Negotiate
                                Peace</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to Dr. <persName type="to">S. E. Mezes</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <p>1. Will you kindly let me have a memorandum on the point raised in the
                            marked portion of this report,<note n="5" xml:id="d152fn5">The last
                                sentence of Professor Coolidge’s report No. 4, Dec. 31, 1918, <ref target="#pg_221">p. 221</ref>.</note> and your recommendations
                            for appropriate action in the matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-05">January
                                    5, 1919</date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>